  "texts": [
    "We employed a Monte Carlo simulation (MCS) of 10,000 iterations to estimate the probabilities for Neura achieving observed thresholds of maximum scores, highest scores, and preferred answers among its 20 scores by chance -assuming a uniform distribution of scores within each question's specific range across all participants.",
    "We set our alpha level threshold at 0.05 to determine statistical significance using two-tailed tests.",
    "All computations and visualizations were performed using R version 4.1.3, with the packages: 'afex,' 'eulerr,' 'ggplot2,' 'irr,' 'lme4', and 'lmertest.'",
    "Anonymized data not published within this article will be made available by request from any qualified investigator.",
    "Of the 13 neurologists, 8 were board-certified."
